e the mission works in our country. This is the desire that The Bible Missionary Church is called to be a communion of of international Church linked to one another in a community of faith for fellowship, worship, service and witness.\r\n\r\nDo you have a vision to get involved the mission work in our the unreached Buddhist land? We covet your prompt concern and prayer for the Buddhist land. We are very much interesting to or connect to your ORG. Could you also visit our country and see how our work is doing? \r\n\r\nI therefore would like you to consider this desired request. I am looking forward to hearing from you.\r\n\r\n\r\nYours sincerely,\r\n\r\nRev. Amos Thang Chin\r\nThe Founding President\r\nBible Missionary Church of Myanmar\r\nPO Box 951\r\nYangon, Myanmar',0,'2012-02-08 15:29:39','2012-02-08 15:29:39'),(228,209,'Hello,\r\nI am a 20 years old girl from romania. I have 5 more sisters and 2 brothers and an amazing mother, our father didn`t care about us so much...so our mother raised us all by herself. but God loved us so much that He did not let my mother alone so He took care of us. And one of the ways He did that is through you- Christian Aid Ministries. I am so thankful and I wanted you to know this, and to know that I was thaught for a little age to pray for you, because you helped us so much. So, thank you! I also want you to know that I am a woman of God now...I am living for Him...and I am involved in mission too and I want to help other people like you did for me and my family. God Bless you, all. I am praying for you. ',0,'2012-02-08 17:54:01','2012-02-08 17:54:01'),(229,209,'Hello,\r\nI am a 20 years old girl from romania. I have 5 more sisters and 2 brothers and an amazing mother, our father didn`t care about us so much...so our mother raised us all by herself. but God loved us so much that He did not let my mother alone so He took care of us. And one of the ways He did that is through you- Christian Aid Ministries. I am so thankful and I wante