:\r\n\r\nMy name is Maike Christopher and I am on Social Security Disability. On April 4th, I was involved in a rollover accident in a Penske rental truck that contained all of my and my pregnant daughter\'s possessions on I-95 near Summerville, S.C.. The truck was destroyed and anything that survived the crash, including all of my clothing, paperwork, identification, everything I own in the world was moved onto another Penske truck that is now being held in Summerville. I was blessed to survive the accident, but after being airlifted to Richland Trauma Center in Columbia, upon my release I found myself without any access to phone, money, transportation, my food stamp card, etc, so I was flown to Ft.Myers where we have temporary shelter.We are also in desperate need of rental assistance in the Miami/Miami Beach  region, my daughter is supposed to start college there this summer, and we currently do no have a place to live, and a baby on the way in September. I have contacted HUD who is unable to offer any assistance, and it seems that many of the sites we have discovered on the internet are nothing but scams, so if you could direct us into the right direction there it would be greatly appreciated. At the moment we are staying in the 33914 zip code, we are looking to live near the 33132/33139 zip code.\r\n  What I need immediate assistance with, is getting the truck from S.C. to FL. I don\'t know if your organization can help me with this, or can direct me to someone who can. I am still recovering from my head injuries and burns sustained in the accident, as well as being under Dr.\'s orders not to drive, and I don\'t have the funds to hire movers. I paid for additional insurance that Penske now tells me only protects them, not me, and keep getting the run around even from my own car insurance that shouldn\'t even be involved. Maybe you know of an attorney that would look at what my options are pro-bono? If there is anyone in the Columbia/Charleston area that you could recommend that might help me and my daughter we would be eternally grateful. The truck is located in the 29483 zip code.\r\nThank you in advance for your response,\r\nMaike Christopher\r\n239-745-9273',0,'2012-04-26 19:52:37','2012-04-26 19:52:37'),(475,440,'Newsletter Signup From New Account',0,'2012-04-26 23:04:21','2012-04-26 23:04:21'),(476,441,'Newsletter Signup From New Account',0,'2012-04-27 05:07:46','2012-04-27 05:07:46'),(477,441,'I would like to continue donating $30 a month to help Emmanuel, my new sponser child. He is code 652NAM B4. I put my checking account number into my account so there won\'t be any more credit card complications. Please email me if I need to do more to make sure my donations go to Emmanuel.',0,'2012-04-27 05:15:05','2012-04-27 05:15:05'),(478,442,'Newsletter Signup From New Account',0,'2012-04-27 11:14:44','2012-04-27 11:14:44'),(479,443,'PLEASE, do you have tracts in the Romanian language available?',0,'2012-04-27 12:29:01','2012-04-27 12:29:01'),(480,444,'Newsletter Signup From New Account',0,'2012-04-27 16:34:56','2012-04-27 16:34:56'),(481,445,'PLEASE REMOVE THE NAMES OF THESE FORMER RESIDENTS, NOW DECEASED.\r\n\r\nCATHERINE B TAYLOR         41550\r\nMARY HOFFMAN\r\n433 S KINZER AVE APT 244\r\nNEW HOLLAND PA 17557-8736\r\n\r\nTHANK YOU',0,'2012-04-27 20:10:27','2012-04-27 20:10:27'),(482,446,'Newsletter Signup From New Account',0,'2012-04-27 21:11:18','2012-04-27 21:11:18'),(483,447,'Do you have a PDF file of any of your newsleters that can be emailed to prospective contributors?\r\n\r\nI have a new client from non-Mennonite background that I spoke to that has an interest in donating to Christian Aid Ministries.\r\n\r\nIf available, please email copies to me.  Thanks.',0,'2012-04-28 16:24:21','2012-04-28 16:24:21'),(484,448,'Newsletter Signup From New Account',0,'2012-04-29 12:41:18','2012-04-29 12:41:18'),(485,449,'Newsletter Signup From New Account',0,'2012-04-30 15:07:45','2012-04-30 15:07:45'),(486,450,'Newsletter Signu