ms commenting on Bible and saying that Christianity is false and there is not truth with them. All this makes us very hard to preach Christ among the people. So with all this we have been doing our best to preach Christ.\r\n\r\nBut Since many years there is no Church building for us ,we are gathering in believers houses, sometimes in rented houses, many times many rejected us for giving a house for rent to have worship, and some gave but charged much rent so even this also does not worked out for us to have a permanent place to have worship.\r\n\r\nBrother, you all know how hard it is to a church to have growth when it has no place to e gather and when it don’t know this week in which believer’s house the Church will gather, because all the Church members have very tiny houses and some live in a huts, so church gathering shits from one place another place day by day.\r\n\r\n And many times, we are unable to conduct Bible Classes, VBS and Gospel meetings in the houses because in the day time the believers will go for work and close the houses, so that time we look for public places, when we go to public places we need to take permission of Government and Police. So this all a problem and matter of money.\r\n\r\nSo my dear brethren, there are many problems we come across which we can’t express in mail, I have been learning about your ministries and feel very happy when ever  see you on interest. Brother, we with a lot of interest and hope seek your cooperation in helping us for a Church building. You know that we are not asking for that which will benefit us fleshly but spiritually. A   church building remain for years and will bear fruits for years by which the society and mankind was so much benefited. It will bless generations with word of God. And I know that I need to tell you much about the benefits of a Church.\r\n\r\nBrethren, we humble seek your cooperation in helping us with church building and help us build the people for heaven. We are ready to provide you any kind of information that you need and do the best we can on our part.\r\n\r\nHope that the committee will consider us and will allow us to send a proposal for a church building.And blesses our efforts in all that we do. May God bless you all and enable to AID the world which is need of LOVE AND FORGIVENESS.\r\n\r\nYour Brother in Christ,\r\n\r\nPrasad.K\r\n\r\nPreacher.\r\n\r\n \r\n\r\n \r\n\r\n \r\n\r\n \r\n\r\n \r\n\r\n \r\n',0,'2012-05-12 15:16:49','2012-05-12 15:16:49'),(528,484,'Newsletter Signup Form Submittal',0,'2012-05-12 15:18:06','2012-05-12 15:18:06'),(529,485,'Newsletter Signup From New Account',0,'2012-05-13 20:26:06','2012-05-13 20:26:06'),(530,486,'Kindly allow me to introduce myself to you and our infant charity organisation, Hope for Youth - Uganda (HFYU), which operates in Mukono District of Uganda, East Africa.\r\n\r\nFounded in November 2007, HFYU provides in and out of school educational programs for vulnerable children and youth whose families have been devastated by poverty and HIV-AIDS. These young people face serious family abuses ranging from child-labour cases to being married off at tender ages, in case of girls. HFYU also provides counseling and support services to guardians responsible for taking care of the children at their homes.\r\n \r\nHFYU is a Christian organization and follows the principles of Christianity, but open to all needy children in the community without any discrimination whatsoever. \r\n\r\nOur mission is to improve the quality of life for children and youth in our communities through education and health services; while planting the seed of hope in these young people.\r\n\r\nAmong our programs mandate is the education project, which seeks to help children complete their Primary education and to provide vocational training so that youth can find employment, generate an income that can provide a sustainable livelihood for themselves and their families.\r\n \r\nHFYU runs a small infants’ day school for children, providing free education currently to over 300 children whose parents/guardians (mostly grandmothers) are too poor to pay for meals and other scholastic materials required at government aided schools under Universal Primary Education. Currently our classrooms run from nursery to primary 6, growing by one class each year with a future plan for a vocational training centre after primary 7 (1 and ½ years from now).\r\n\r\nFor proper planning/preparation of our work, it is the reason we humbly write to you now seeking your partnership and assistance to be able to start up a vocational center which shall immensely improve the living standards of these young people and the communities they live in.   \r\n\r\nWe shall be most grateful if our humble request receives your kind consideration, and if you require further information about this application, I shall be happy to provide it please.\r\n\r\nThank you and kind regards\r\n\r\nPeter Nsubuga\r\nProject Director\r\nHope for Youth - Uganda\r\nP.O. Box 33226, Kampala\r\nTel. +267 782 727 059\r\n',0,'2012-05-14 15:05:37','2012-05-14 15:05:37'),(531,487,'',0,'2012-05-14 19:16:44','2012-05-14 19:16:44'),(532,487,'Starting May 21, 2012, we will have a new address: Walter Benedict, back apartment, 275 N. Main St., Winsted, CT. 06098. Sincerely, Mrs. Walter Benedict ',0,'2012-05-14 19:21:37','2012-05-14 19:21:37'),(533,489,'Newsletter Signup From New Account',0,'2012-05-14 23:18:46','2012-05-14 23:18:46'),(534,490,'Newsletter Signup From New Account',0,'2012-05-15 15:43:50','2012-05-15 15:43:50'),(535,491,'Could you please send me an email with the Hygiene/Health Kits contents listed? I have a PDF file from you (several years ago), but I cannot open it. Also, have the school kits changed at all?\r\nThanks for your help!',0,'2012-05-15 20:54:39','2012-05-15 20:54:39'),(536,492,'This is to any Kind heart man or woman,white or black who is very\r\ncompassionate and whom is a cheerful giver , i hope my sincere request\r\nwill  meet yo