n the heartbeat of DLOM we believe that words alone cannot fully convey God’s love in a context where people are struggling to survive.  \r\nOur desire has always been to \r\n•A servant of the local church\r\n•Reaching the lost with gospel of Jesus Christ (including soccer ministry through competing teams and evangelistic sports camps and clinics and cycling clubs).\r\n•Caring for the poor, and marginalized\r\n\r\nDivine Love Outreach Ministry recognizes the local church as the bride of Christ and God’s primary representative in the world. Therefore in all that we do we seek serve Christ church to partner with it in doing God’s work to enable it fulfill it part of the great commission. \r\n\r\nCurrent activities \r\n•Training workshops/seminars Christian workers to strengthen local churches\r\n•Organize retreats to offer opportunities for growth in Christian spirituality\r\n•Gospel crusades/film evangelism\r\n•Distribution of bibles and Christian literature\r\n•Drilling wells/boreholes\r\n•We facilitate and enable needy children (OVC’s) obtain sponsorship \r\n•Distribution of Clothing to destitute \r\nThe ministry depends on limited gifts and donations in kind and cash from believers through collections, appeals, and direct contributions, all of which goes directly into mission work. Consequently DLOM financial resources are very much limited. \r\n\r\nWe would be interested to partner with your organization.\r\n\r\nThank you \r\n\r\nYours in Christ service\r\n\r\nEvans Amponsah',0,'2012-06-01 23:47:20','2012-06-01 23:47:20'),(598,551,'Hello christian friends,\r\n  i am a church planter in Liberia and the Lord has help me to organize some churches in my country.\r\ni am looking for your support toward my churches.\r\ni want for you to please help me with some funds to help me purchase some bundles of zinc for my churches in Liberia.\r\ni am dealing with plenty of old and poor people in my churches and i may need your help for them.\r\nmay God richly bless you for you