2012-06-29 13:11:47'),(693,638,'Dear Christian Aid Ministries,\r\n\r\nI’m placing an inquiry regarding my most important need for assistance with “Back to School” items such as supplies & clothing for my daughter, who relocated here from Tampa.  In addition, I’d like to know if you’re able to help us with a food basket?  I’m unable to gain any financial or WIC assistance through my local government agency.\r\n\r\n I have several other issues I’d like to address by asking for your help & guidance on the following…\r\n\r\n•	My daughter suddenly relocated to Plantation from Tampa and she hasn’t lived with me for the past eight years.  She was unexpectedly removed from her Grandparents home by Pasco County Sheriff’s Office Child Protection Division, and she’s got the same bed set she had when she lived with me years ago as a 6 year old.  My daughter will be 15 in August, and she’s outgrown her bed.  I’d like to see if I can do an even trade of furniture… (trade a 6-piece twin bed set; which includes twin mattress & box spring, bed rails, headboard, two night stands, chest of drawers, dresser w/hutch)…to be traded for a bigger bed with mattress & box spring, chest of drawers, & dresser).  Can you help?  The pics of my daughter’s furniture are attached, and it’s in good condition, as she barely used it.\r\n   \r\nI’m not asking for a handout.  I’m available to work off any assistance provided to me on the weekends, and am open to any suggestions you may have.  See, money was tight before my daughter came down here…I spent all the savings I had to drive to Tampa and bring her back.  Her Grandparents didn’t allow her to bring much, so we went to Salvation Army & Goodwill to get clothing…but, I can’t afford much, and she still has clothing needs.  A portion was spent on hygiene items to get her bathroom situated for her as well.  My daughter is so sweet, and she’s glad to be living with me again.  But, we are truly struggling financially, and I’m not sure what to do.  \r\n\r\nI’m trying to provide the best I can for her, and we need a little help & support to get over the hump of the transition.  I’ve been with my employer for 5 ½ years, and my job relocated me to this area.  I’m considering getting a second job on the weekends, and I’d like to discuss my situation with someone who can help in any way.  Thank you for your time and consideration, and please have a great day.\r\n\r\nMy personal email is stephanie5327@gmail.com and my cell phone is (813) 531-0800.\r\n\r\nSincerely,\r\n\r\nStephanie Bradford\r\n',0,'2012-06-29 13:58:08','2012-06-29 13:58:08'),(694,639,'Newsletter Signup From New Account',0,'2012-06-29 19:26:59','2012-06-29 19:26:59'),(695,640,'BLOCK A 119 IDI OPE\r\nINT MKT ELEYELE\r\nOYO STATE  NIGERIA\r\n\r\nDear beloved in Christ\r\nmy name is ify obi   i was a church goer until one of my friend invited me to their church  after the sermon my understanding was opened then i realized that i am a lost sinner so i repented of my sins and gave my whole life to Christ Jesus is now my lord and messiah  i did not stop i went ahead  telling other friends to about Jesus and to the glory of God  71 brothers and sister gave their lives to Christ\r\nwe all are now  born again Christians  believed that Jesus is the son of God and savior of the word  but we all don\'t have bibles to read Gods word  so we need your help  dear beloved please kindly send to 72 of us 72 seventy two complete holy bibles and literature\'s  through the above address by M-BAG SEA MAIL\r\nwe all are ready too  go out there with our bibles and lead other lost souls to Christ\r\nGod will bless you as you help us  amen\r\nthanks\r\nyours all in Christ\r\nbro ify obi   and friend',0,'2012-06-30 03:14:05','2012-06-30 03:14:05'),(696,641,'Newsletter Signup From New Account',0,'2012-06-30 19:08:34','2012-06-30 19:08:34'),(697,642,'Newsletter Signup From New Account',0,'2012-06-30 21:29:34','2012-06-30 21:29:34'),(698,643,'Newsletter Signup From New Account',0,'2012-