,'2012-07-08 00:22:59'),(724,668,'Newsletter Signup From New Account',0,'2012-07-08 02:18:52','2012-07-08 02:18:52'),(725,669,'Newsletter Signup From New Account',0,'2012-07-09 03:04:49','2012-07-09 03:04:49'),(726,670,'Newsletter Signup Form Submittal',0,'2012-07-09 04:23:52','2012-07-09 04:23:52'),(727,636,'Hello,\r\n\r\nMy wife and I and our 5 young children have been feeling God drawing us towards missions over the past few years, and more increasingly hearing a call to preach the gospel and meet the needs of others. We were both brought up in a \"modern\" church where our view of missions was not what it is today. Thankfully, God started leading us down a different path this past 2 years, and drew us deeper into Him through surrendering our lives to His calling in obedience.\r\n\r\nWe have been blessed to be a part of the Gympie Anapabtist Fellowship for the past 18 months, and through this time, have grown spiritually with the help of this church, and the wonderful literature from seed of truth and the remnant. \r\n\r\nIt has been through following the writings and emails of Pablo Yoder in Waslala that we became aware of CAM, and started to look into this organisation. As we in Australia have very little resources and guidance in the way of missions, we are very much in the dark to where, what and how.\r\n\r\nIs there any guidance or avenue that you could point us down, or get us in touch with in regards to where there is a need, or where our family could be used in the mission field throughout the world. We really have a desire to go to preach the gospel in more of a \"3rd world\" region where there is a need for Christ, His provisions, Love, and Care. Even in the face of Persecution.\r\n\r\nI hope you can hear our hearts, and help us in following God\'s leading by pointing us in the right direction. \r\n\r\nGod Bless, and we look forward to hearing back from you.\r\nDaniel & Kylee Lyne',0,'2012-07-09 10:42:44','2012-07-09 10:42:44'),(728,671,'Dear Sir/Madam.\r\n\r\nI am Patience Y. Johnson, a blind young Liberian lady who got blind some years ago just after graduating from high school which prevented me from enrolling into university.\r\n\r\nDespite the efforts of my parents who contacted various doctors in the country to conduct eye operations on me, et, they were unable to do this as a result of the poor medical services and facilities for such treatment. The final recommendation was to go abroad for such treatment as they lack the equipment here.\r\n\r\nHowever, Some body from the state has consented helping me for the operation as they have already contacted a specialized doctor in this area.\r\nThe individual has agreed paying for the medical cost and others apart from the round trip ticket to the United State for this treatment.\r\n\r\nIn view of the above, I am seeking your kind assistant for the purchase of the round trip ticket to the USA for the operation as I am expected to travel this July, 2012.\r\nPlease help me as all efforts were made to secure the ticket but I have not succeeded and due to financial constrains, my parents have not been able ti meet this particular cost.\r\n\r\nThanks and I will appreciate if this email could be given some kind considerations as it is actually urgent.\r\nFor further detail, I can be reach at +231 886 911721.\r\n\r\nSincerely Yours\r\n\r\nPatience Y. Johnson.\r\n\r\n\r\n',0,'2012-07-09 11:29:15','2012-07-09 11:29:15'),(729,672,'Dear Sir/Madam.\r\nI write on behalf of the Center for Inclusion and Empowerment to kindly request your support for a Christian Community School in the Soul Clinic Community.  This community base school was actually founded by Mr. and Mrs. Torma who passed away two years ago.\r\n\r\nThe vision is to provide education to community children from poor family background within the community who cannot afford sending their children to private or other public schools with high school charges.\r\n\r\nhowever, his death has seriously affecting the growth of the school especially running cost of the school including administrative costs.\r\nMoreover, some serious rain storm took away the entire roof of the school build living just the empty structure standing.  Off course, They do have land which they bought some years ago and it is even our hope to expand on the facilities because there are more children enrolling everyday.\r\n\r\nIn this regard, we are inquiring whether your institution could be of a help to them as they are actually doing well in bringing up these children who could be our future leaders.\r\nIt is interesting to see how wonderful the children are doing despite some of the challenges of the school.\r\n\r\nOur organization is just a small community base one which does advocacy for those in need and channel them with some relevant institutions/individuals for appropriate actions concerning their needs.  our website is \r\nhttp;www.cie-lib.org.\r\nThanks and we can even facilitate any meeting between your institution and them if necessary or take you to the community for first hand information.\r\n\r\nSincerely Yours\r\n\r\nKaprie Kanu\r\nDirector\r\nMOBILE; +231 886 580435.',0,'2012-07-09 12:30:05','2012-07-09 12:30:05'),(730,673,'Hello, could you please give an indication of what format should be used to request for funding? It is for an organization in Africa doing great work to empower disabled people.\r\nthank you sincerely.\r\ni can be reached @ 818 224 9134\r\n\r\ntikiri',0,'2012-07-09 17:14:17','2012-07-09 17:14:17'),(731,674,'I was wondering if I could receive some information on volenteer work in your PA warehouses? My Sunday School class would be interested in spending an evening sorting colthes or packing food... any information and a schedule of your date for these projects in the months of July and August would be appreciated! Thank you!',0,'2012-07-09 20:24:52','2012-07-09 20:24:52'),(732,675,'May we have contact information for Christian Aid Ministries\'s VP of Marketing or Development