invite you to come and minister with us. Please select the area you would like to deal with!! Note that our friends who are living in different parts of the world are willing to send testimonies and recommendation about me (Rev Norbert and the ministries or projects we are doing in Tanzania.\r\n\r\nEthos and Purpose\r\n\r\nPCA  is a community of God\'s people who delight to worship him and are passionate about the Gospel, seeking to fulfill the mission of Jesus Christ in the world.\r\n\r\nOur purpose is to glorify God by planting, strengthening, and partnering with churches around the world as we:\r\n\r\n    evangelize the unreached,\r\n    minister to human need,\r\n    disciple believers into churches,\r\n    equip churches to fulfill Christ\'s Commission.\r\n\r\n \r\n\r\nPurpose Statement Explained\r\n\r\nOur purpose: PCA has many functions, responsibilities, and ministries, but only one basic purpose. Everything we do is related to that purpose.\r\n\r\nto glorify God: This is our highest motivation and all-encompassing purpose. We do not glorify man, organization, or government, but God, and we evaluate what we do by this standard.\r\n\r\nplanting, strengthening, and partnering with churches: We are convinced that God\'s primary means of relating to and transforming the world is the church. Where there is no church, we work to start one. Where there is a church, we seek to work together. Our ideal church-mission relationship is a dynamic, interdependent partnership that reaches out together to love the unreached world.\r\n\r\nevangelize: We believe that mankind is lost and needs to be redeemed through Christ Jesus, whom we proclaim as Savior. All of our ministry is motivated by this belief.\r\n\r\nthe unreached: Our major focus is on reaching unevangelized people groups. We want to minister among individuals and communities who have never had the opportunity to understand the Gospel.\r\n\r\nminister to human need: We acknowledge that the ultimate human need is to know God. We also believe that He has called us to compassionate, holistic service in this broken world. Jesus is our example as we minister to people who are suffering because of, HIV and AIDS, poverty, illness, or natural disaster.\r\n\r\ndisciple believers: This involves teaching the Word of God, helping people to discover their God-given gifts, enabling them to serve others, and helping them become mature in Christ.\r\n\r\ninto churches: Our focus on the church distinguishes us from specialized service agencies focused on aviation, linguistics, and medicine. While we are involved in many of those specialty areas, we always seek to plant churches or partner with a local church wherever we work. (This is our future plan) You may affiliate with us in this field if you have a plan to set up  aviation, linguistics, and medicine ministries.\r\n\r\nequip churches to fulfill Christ\'s Commission: This involves challenging the church to obey Christ\'s command to make disciples of all nations. We seek to provide leadership training and practical help to enable churches to establish mission sending agencies. We desire to be a church-planting mission and a mission-planting mission!.\r\nMinistry Vision\r\nBy faith, PCA sees:\r\n\r\n    making the Gospel available to the Tanzania people.\r\n\r\n \r\n\r\n    Christian growth in local churches.\r\n\r\n \r\n\r\n    addressing the needs of the people in the community.\r\n\r\n \r\n\r\n    believers expanding to reach out to other groups.\r\n\r\n-Through our Rise Africa Program for poor people we have managed to support educational materials and fees for some children in nursery and primary schools in Tanzania and have other community programs as you can see from the website. To know about our Rise Africa Program visit www.rise-africa.org\r\n\r\nAt this time we have some friends from different parts of the work who can speak highly about Rev Norbert and his ministries of Bethel Branch and the small projects going on.\r\n\r\nIf you would like to work with our church at the national level let me know I can connect with the national leaders since am not the national leader rather a missionary and local church pastor .\r\n\r\nThere many ways you can partner with us:-\r\n\r\n-Send your mission team.\r\n\r\n-Come and minister with us .You may conduct seminars, crusades, meetings etc\r\n\r\n-Help the ministers who have no fees to join bible schools/colleges.\r\n\r\n-Volunteer with us in spiritual or community programs.\r\n\r\n-Send gospel materials (tracts, bibles, computers, build churches etc)\r\n\r\nWe hope to hear at what area are you interested to partner with us.\r\n\r\nWe will be happy to seeing you in our country\r\n\r\nThanks in advance.\r\n\r\nGod bless so much.\r\n\r\nRev Norbert Enock Mbwiliza\r\n\r\nPCA-Bethel Family Worship Centre..',0,'2012-07-27 15:51:41','2012-07-27 15:51:41'),(792,729,'Newsletter Signup From New Account',0,'2012-07-27 16:46:35','2012-07-27 16:46:35'),(793,729,'Dear sir/madam\r\n\r\n my name is samwel birundu a kenya .\r\nmy question is .if  a kind of self help group has a mission but has a shortage of items and fund ,to complete the project ,are the eligible for surpport from the ministry?\r\nthank you and i shall be grateful for your reply\r\nsamwel',0,'2012-07-27 16:57:26','2012-07-27 16:57:26'),(794,730,'Newsletter Signup From New Account',0,'2012-07-27 18:25:31','2012-07-27 18:25:31'),(795,730,'Newsletter Signup Form Submittal',0,'2012-07-27 18:28:07','2012-07-27 18:28:07'),(796,4,'Testing, 1, 2, 3. ',0,'2012-07-27 18:58:26','2012-07-27 18:58:26'),(797,731,'Newsletter Signup From New Account',0,'2012-07-28 13:18:08','2012-07-28 13:18:08'),(798,732,'Dear chief Executive,\r\nChristian Aid Ministries\r\nTHE GOSPEL OF OUR LORD JESUS CHRIST IS THE POWER OF GOD UNTO SALVATION.\r\n\r\n\r\nGreetings to you in the mighty and matchless name of our Lord and Saviors Jesus Christ. Grace and peace be multiplied unto you from God our father, who has called us into His eternal kingdom and glory, and from the lord Jesus Christ. Amen.\r\nThe ministry of our lord Jesus Christ should not be taken lightly. This is important because it is linked to the lives of millions of men and women all over the world. When you realize that Jesus died for all men irrespective of theirs race, tribe, religious, custom or geographical location, you will understand that the gospel is utmost importance. The Preaching of the message of Christ is serious business.\r\nYou must make up your mind to continually participate in the ministry of the gospel all over the world; it is the divine responsibility of every blood-bought child of God. This gospel is pre-ordained commission delivered to us by the Lord Jesus Christ, making us custodian of its divine truths.\r\n \r\nPartnership with us is sure way of continually participating in the furtherance of the gospel. You may not be the preacher on the pulpit, or the one with the bestselling books or the large evangelical crusades; but you can be that one who is praying and interceding for souls to won, giving financially, and preparing the venue for the meeting, and doing  all the running behind the scenes. When the victory is won, rejoice, because it is as much your victory as it is\r\nThe victory the preachers, pastor or ministers who went to the battle front.\r\n \r\nIn 1 Samuel 30:22-24, David made it clear that those men who didn’t go to war with them, but stayed with the be supplies were equal partakers of the reward with those who went to battle.\r\nUnderstand this, Jesus came to reconcile all men to God and that is the reason for the preaching of the gospel. There are so many people the Lord wants to reach before the end of time; there is so much to be done, and God is counting on you.\r\nAs long as you remain faithful to the ministry to the ministry the Lord has committed to you’re your trust by continually supporting those on the frontlines, God will reward your faithfulness and you will always be partaker of victories of partnership.\r\nPartnership is potent tools that God has equipped his people with. It is the best platform for plugging into the miraculous power of God. Partnership will always cause the miraculous to happen in one life-physically, financially, spiritually etc.\r\nPartnership with God people will create a strong bond (Ecclesiastes 4:12).\r\nWe do not partnership with God just because we need miracle. No, we already know that we carry miracle working ability or power of God. We do not enter into partnership so that we can be wealthy and walk in health. No, No.\r\n \r\nPartnership is not a product. We are child of God and all things belong to us already. We enter into partnership with because we want to participate actively in the divine mission; because we Love Him and want to contribute to the furtherance of the gospel of our Lord Jesus Christ.\r\n \r\n\r\n\r\nAs ye go, the kingdom of God heaven is at hand. Healed the sick, cleanse the lepers, raise the dead, cast out devils: freely ye have received, freely give.’’ Mathew 10:7-8\r\nWhen the lord Jesus walked the surface of the earth, He was embodiment of divine power. He was God manifested in earth realm, and He brought light and hope to a world that lingered in the dark, eagerly anticipating the coming of messiah.\r\n\r\nHe was like no other prophet before Him. Many marved at Him because He spoke with so much power and authority. He knew exactly who He was and why He came to the earth; and, he voiced it out on many occasion, He said,….I am come that they might have life, and that they might have it more abundantly’’ (John 10:10). On another occasion, He said, ‘’As long as I am in the world, I am the light of the world’’ (John 9:5.Hallelujah.\r\nEverywhere Jesus went, He went seen doing good, preaching the messenge of the kingdom and healing all that were oppressed of the devil and God was  with Him; in fact a major part of His ministry was spent healing the sick. The Bible says in Mathew 4:23, Jesus went through Galilee, teaching in their synagogues, preaching the good news of the kingdom and healing every disease and sickness among the people.’ This was the will of God manifested because Jesus said, ‘’for I came down from heaven, not do mine will, but the will of him that sent me’’ (John 6:38).\r\n\r\nIn Mathew 9:37-38, the Bible records that on a certain occasion, multitudes came to Jesus and He was moved with compassion on the because they were as sheep having no shepherd. He called his disciples together and said, ‘’The Harvest truly is plenteous, but the laborers’ are few; Pray ye therefore the Lord of the harvest, that he will send forth Laborers into his Harvest,’ Watch the next thing He did according to Mathew 10:1.The Bible say,’ And when he had called unto him his twelve disciples, he gave them power against unclean spirit, to cast them out, and to heal all manner of sickness and all manner of disease.\r\n\r\nWhat I want you to notice here is that Jesus saw the need for more labourers,and therefore gave His disciples power to heal the sick, cast out unclean spirits. He had said to them,’’Ye are the light of the world,, (Mathew 5:14),and now He proved they were the light of the world by giving them authority to heal the sick; and Bible records that they returned with testimonies(Luke 10:17).\r\n\r\n\r\nApostle Paul said, I am not ashamed of the gospel of our lord Jesus Christ, for it is the power of God unto salvation to every one that believeth (Roman 1:16) we Christian,  we must absolutely convinced and persuaded that the gospel is the  power of God, it is\r\nGod only saving power let this truth dawn on our spirit for all the time. Paul writing to the Roman Said, the gospel of Christ is power to save, help, heal and deliver and proper people but he can’t do it without his word - the (gospel) if any body, anywhere will believed this gospel, no matters how lost in sin or how deep in evil, if they will hear it, believed it\r\nand act on it: it make no difference how deep the valley is or how miry the pit is, they will come out as white as snow. This is something that can’t be humanly or physically explained because it’s the power of God. \r\n\r\nHow then they call on him in whom they have not believed? and how shall they believed in him of whom they they have not heard? And shall they hear without a preacher?{Roman10:14} Most of the world doesn’t known that God loves them. They are unaware that He\'s not counting their sins against them {2conrinthian 5:19}.Many have afraid of\r\nretribution. However, only a few are acquainted with the God love.\r\n\r\nThe messenge of the gospel of our lord Jesus Christ is so simple. It can be being defined in one: LOVE. When you know some one love and care so much about you and your welfare, you’ll want to do every thing to please him. This is the reason, He tell us go and tell that\r\nHe loves them. God known’s they will turn away from their sins and believe on him when they hear of His love for them; But how can they hear without a\r\npreacher? Apostle Paul asked, He’s referring to the informed Christian who truly understand the of our lord Jesus Christ.\r\n\r\nWe need to understand that, we are God\'s representative, sent into the world as a minister of\r\nreconcialiation.According to the Bible, this is our prime responsibility, as Christian .Tell every one of the gospel and be not ashamed {Roman 1:16} Its good news; Its a messenge of love he world will never hear or known what God has until you and I, invest in reaching them through every available means. Let your voice and giving be heard today.  \r\n\r\nThink about it, someone who’s been a sinner, hears the message of the gospel, believed, it  and affirms Jesus as lord of his life and  immediately becomes as righteous as Jesus is righteous. His old nature becomes immediately supplanted with the nature of God which the nature of righteousness. If a man is sick or poor, the power of God to make him rich and bring him healing is the gospel of Jesus Christ it’s a power that beyond description. It can do anything and change any body that’s the power of the gospel. All a man need is to hear it and believed it. If he will only believe it, it will change him forever. But he can’t believe it until we make it available. When he hears it then he has the opportunity to believe. This is why I love to preach the gospel. I enjoy you today to be part of our activities in reaching out to thousand of people is this direction, most importantly, in my\r\ncountry (west Africa-Nigeria) the gospel is been preach every corner unless the northern part of Nigeria where predominantly Moslem. The people there don’t know of this gospel in that region. That is why terrorism is the order of day today.\r\nWe are reaching out to you for this purpose, for the avoidance of doubt make commitment to us today.\r\nMake missionary evangelism crusade donation in Africa through this medium. We need Bibles free distribution and money.\r\n\r\nI pray for you now.\r\nMay the grace of our lord increase in your life\r\nEmpowering you to achieve beyond your Imagination.\r\nMay the presence of God overshadow you? May The blessing of God fill your life Daily and your business.\r\nIf there is anything that has been difficult for you, May the Holy Spirit now make it easy.\r\nMay God give you that solution you been looking for your business and \r\nFamilies in the name of Jesus.\r\nEvery where you go, they will know you as problem solver, everywhere you go \r\n, you would be light givers.\r\nEverywhere you go, you would be an encouragement, The sources of \r\nStrength, May God uses you.\r\nMay God lift you from one level of glory to another?\r\nNo weapon formed against you shall prosper. And God will increase you from \r\nGlory to glory.\r\nYou would move from glory to glory, from strength to strength and \r\nContinually experience The glory of Christ in your life..., in the name of Jesus.\r\n\r\nPastor Favour Raymond    \r\nSNR:SAINTS MATH