orships can be cancelled at any time by accessing the “My Account” section of the website or by calling us at 330-893-2428.</p>','2011-11-07 20:31:46','2011-11-07 20:31:47'),(57,57,'en','<p>{{ content_holder_86 }}</p>','2011-11-07 20:31:47','2012-02-28 16:34:06'),(63,63,'en','<p>{{ content_holder_86 }}</p>','2012-02-28 16:28:26','2012-02-28 16:30:08'),(64,64,'en','<br />\r\n<h1>CAM Locations:</h1>\r\n<p>At CAM\'s home office in Berlin, Ohio, staff members do behind the scenes work such as processing donations, accounting, fundraising, procuring GIK products, making decisions, and directing the various CAM state-side operations and field bases.</p>\r\n<p><img class=\"add-caption\" rel=\"225x255\" alt=\"Home Office, Berlin, OH\" title=\"Home Office, Berlin, OH\" src=\"/system/images/BAhbBlsHOgZmSSI2MjAxMi8wNi8yMi8yMV8zNV8xOF81NjlfSG9tZV9PZmZpY2VfQmVybGluX09ILmpwZwY6BkVU/Home_Office_Berlin_OH.jpg\" height=\"326\" width=\"595\" /></p>\r\n<p>We have a 55,000 sq. ft. distribution center in Ephrata, Pennsylvania, where food parcels are packed and other relief shipments organized. Next to the distribution center is our meat canning facility.</p>\r\n<p><img class=\"add-caption\" rel=\"225x255\" alt=\"Distribution center and meat canning facility, Ephrata, Pennsylvania\" title=\"Distribution center and meat canning facility, Ephrata, Pennsylvania\" src=\"/system/images/BAhbBlsHOgZmSSImMjAxMi8wNi8yMi8yMV8zNV8xOF8zODZfMDM5cGEuanBnBjoGRVQ/039pa.jpg\" height=\"326\" width=\"595\" /></p>\r\n<p><img class=\"add-caption\" rel=\"225x255\" alt=\"Canada Office and Clothing Center, Wallenstein, Ontario\" title=\"Canada Office and Clothing Center, Wallenstein, Ontario\" src=\"/system/images/BAhbBlsHOgZmSSInMjAxMi8wNi8yMi8yMV8zNV8xOF8xMjZfMDM5Y2FuLmpwZwY6BkVU/039can.jpg\" height=\"326\" width=\"595\" /></p>\r\n<p><img class=\"add-caption\" rel=\"225x255\" alt=\"DRS Warehouse, Vanleer, Tennessee\" title=\"DRS Warehouse, Vanleer, Tennessee\" src=\"/system/images/BAhbBlsHOgZmSSI5MjAxMi8wNi8yMi8yMV8zOV81Ml8yODRfRFJTX1dhcmVob3VzZV9WYW5sZWVyX1ROLkpQRwY6BkVU/DRS_Warehouse_Vanleer_TN.JPG\" height=\"326\" width=\"595\" /></p>\r\n<p>CAM has staff and distribution networks in Romania, Moldova, Ukraine, Haiti, Nicaragua, Liberia, and Israel.</p>\r\n<p><img class=\"add-caption\" rel=\"225x255\" alt=\"Financial office, Suceava, Romania\" title=\"Financial office, Suceava, Romania\" src=\"/system/images/BAhbBlsHOgZmSSJBMjAxMi8wNi8yMi8yMV80Nl80MV8xMjFfRmluYW5jaWFsX29mZmljZV9TdWNlYXZhX1JvbWFuaWEuanBnBjoGRVQ/Financial_office_Suceava_Romania.jpg\" height=\"326\" width=\"595\" /></p>\r\n<p><img class=\"add-caption\" rel=\"225x255\" alt=\"Warehouse, Cluj, Romania\" title=\"Warehouse, Cluj, Romania\" src=\"/system/images/BAhbBlsHOgZmSSIoMjAxMi8wNi8yMi8yMV8zNV8xOF8yMTFfMDM5Y2x1ai5qcGcGOgZFVA/039cluj.jpg\" height=\"326\" width=\"595\" /></p>\r\n<p><img class=\"add-caption\" rel=\"225x255\" alt=\"Warehouse, Suceava, Romania\" title=\"Warehouse, Suceava, Romania\" src=\"/system/images/BAhbBlsHOgZmSSI0MjAxMi8wNi8yMi8yMV8zNV8xOF80MjdfMDM5cm9tYW5pYXdhcmVob3VzZS5qcGcGOgZFVA/039romaniawarehouse.jpg\" height=\"326\" width=\"595\" /></p>\r\n<p><img class=\"add-caption\" rel=\"225x255\" alt=\"Warehouse, Chisinau, Moldova\" title=\"Warehouse, Chisinau, Moldova\" src=\"/system/images/BAhbBlsHOgZmSSIrMjAxMi8wNi8yMi8yMV8zNV8xOF8zNDVfMDM5bW9sZG92YS5qcGcGOgZFVA/039moldova.jpg\" height=\"326\" width=\"595\" /></p>\r\n<p><img class=\"add-caption\" rel=\"225x255\" alt=\"Office and Warehouse, Kiev, Ukraine\" title=\"Office and Warehouse, Kiev, Ukraine\" src=\"/system/images/BAhbBlsHOgZmSSJCMjAxMi8wNi8yMi8yMV8zNV8xOF83OTdfT2ZmaWNlX2FuZF9XYXJlaG91c2VfS2lldl9Va3JhaW5lLmpwZwY6BkVU/Office_and_Warehouse_Kiev_Ukraine.jpg\" height=\"326\" width=\"595\" /></p>\r\n<p><img class=\"add-caption\" rel=\"225x255\" alt=\"Office and Warehouse, Titanyen, Haiti\" title=\"Office and Warehouse, Titanyen, Haiti\" src=\"/system/images/BAhbBlsHOgZmSSJEMjAxMi8wNi8yMi8yMV8zNV8xOF84NDRfT2ZmaWNlX2FuZF9XYXJlaG91c2VfVGl0YW55ZW5fSGFpdGkuSlBHBjoGRVQ/Office_and_Warehouse_Titanyen_Haiti.JPG\" height=\"326\" width=\"595\" /></p>\r\n<p><img class=\"add-caption\" rel=\"225x255\" alt=\"Joshua Memorial Clinic, La Source, Haiti\" title=\"Joshua Memorial Clinic, La Source, Haiti\" src=\"/system/images/BAhbBlsHOgZmSSJHMjAxMi8wNi8yMi8yMV8zNV8xOF83MDlfSm9zaHVhX01lbW9yaWFsX0NsaW5pY19MYV9Tb3VyY2VfSGFpdGkuanBnBjoGRVQ/Joshua_Memorial_Clinic_La_Source_Haiti.jpg\" height=\"381\" width=\"595\" /></p>\r\n<p><img class=\"add-caption\" rel=\"225x255\" alt=\"Balm of Gilead Clinic, Waslala, Nicaragua\" title=\"Balm of Gilead Clinic, Waslala, Nicaragua\" src=\"/system/images/BAhbBlsHOgZmSSJIMjAxMi8wNi8yMi8yMV8zNV8xOF80NzBfQmFsbV9vZl9HaWxlYWRfQ2xpbmljX1dhc2xhbGFfTmljYXJhZ3VhLmpwZwY6BkVU/Balm_of_Gilead_Clinic_Waslala_Nicaragua.jpg\" height=\"326\" width=\"595\" /></p>\r\n<p><img class=\"add-caption\" rel=\"225x255\" alt=\"Office and Warehouse, Managua, Nicaragua\" title=\"Office and Warehouse, Managua, Nicaragua\" src=\"/system/images/BAhbBlsHOgZmSSIrMjAxMi8wNi8yMi8yMV8zNV8xOF8zMDdfMDM5bWFuYWd1YS5qcGcGOgZFVA/039managua.jpg\" height=\"326\" width=\"595\" /></p>\r\n<p>CAM also operates five clothing centers where clothing, footwear, comforters, and fabric are received, sorted, and prepared for shipment overseas. \r\n</p>\r\n','2012-03-09 16:06:39','2012-06-22 17:55:20'),(65,65,'en','<p><br />{{ content_holder_110 }}</p>','2012-03-09 16:06:39','2012-06-11 19:48:10'),(66,66,'en','<h2>“This help keeps on going!”</h2>\r\n<p>Forest Cormelle, a young Haitian mother, would love to share her opinion on the <strong><a title=\"/programs/22\" href=\"/programs/22\">Shared Accountability and Lending</a>\r\n</strong> (SALT) microfinance program. Forest lives in the mountains of southern Haiti and was trapped in the cycle of poverty and despair for years. She knows how it feels to send children to bed without food, have no money for shoes, and be unable to afford school tuition. But for the past two years, Forest has been part of CAM’s new microfinance program and is excited about the changes taking place in her family.</p>\r\n<p><img class=\"add-caption\" rel=\"450x450\" alt=\"Forest with some of the supplies she sells at the market. \" title=\"Forest with some of the supplies she sells at the market. \" src=\"/system/images/BAhbB1sHOgZmSSIlMjAxMS8wOS8yMy8xNV8xMF80OV8zMzNfU0FMVC5KUEcGOgZFVFsIOgZwOgp0aHVtYkkiDTQ1MHg0NTA+BjsGVA/SALT.JPG\" height=\"299\" width=\"450\" /></p>\r\n<p>A small loan from CAM’s SALT microfinance program enabled Forest to expand her little business of selling rice, oil, and flour in the local markets. As a result of the loan and teaching she received through<strong> <a title=\"/programs/22\" href=\"/programs/22\">SALT</a>\r\n</strong> microfinance, the profit from her small business increased four hundred percent! </p>\r\n<p>“For the first time,” Forest says, “we can buy shoes for the children, send them to school, and save a little each month for emergencies.” </p>\r\n<p>Forest leaves her home at 5:00 a.m. to hike several hours over rugged mountain paths to the markets, while her husband tries to farm the steep hillside behind their small house. Making a living is extremely difficult, but Forest is excited and loves to share how the <a title=\"/programs/22\" href=\"/programs/22\">SALT</a> microfinance program has blessed her family. “This is so much better for us than people giving us food,” she said enthusiastically. “When the food is gone, this help keeps on going!”</p>\r\n<p><a title=\"/programs/22\" href=\"/programs/22\">&lt;&lt; Back to SALT microfinance</a>\r\n</p>','2012-03-16 14:41:57','2012-03-16 14:45:23'),(67,67,'en','<p>{{ content_holder_109 }}</p>','2012-03-16 14:41:57','2012-04-18 14:39:00'),(68,68,'en','<h2>Fulfilled dreams and hopes for the future</h2>\r\n<p><img class=\"add-caption\" rel=\"450x450\" alt=\"Hermitha started her business in Haiti through CAM’s SALT Microfinance Solutions program.\" title=\"Hermitha started her business in Haiti through CAM’s SALT Microfinance Solutions program.\" src=\"/system/images/BAhbB1sHOgZmSSIpMjAxMi8wMy8xNi8xN181MF8yNF82NjRfaGVybWl0aGEuanBnBjoGRVRbCDoGcDoKdGh1bWJJIg00NTB4NDUwPgY7BlQ/hermitha.jpg\" height=\"338\" width=\"348\" /></p>\r\n<p>The sky is starting to lighten in the east as Hermitha steps out of her humble mountain home. With a child in tow, she lifts a large bundle onto her head and starts up the mountain trail. This morning Hermitha walks with purpose for she is now the owner of a small business. </p>\r\n<p>Hermitha lives high in the mountains of southern Haiti and has tried for years to find a dependable way to provide for her large family. Her husband has severe health problems, so the burden of providing for their seven children has fallen on Hermitha. </p>\r\n<p>For the first time in many years, Hermitha is hopeful about the future. She has participated in a CAM program named <a style=\"font-weight: bold;\" title=\"/programs/22\" href=\"/programs/22\">SALT Microfinance Solutions</a>. </p>\r\n<p>Hermitha sells sugar, flour, rice, oil, dried fish, and other miscellaneous grocery items. Twice a week she hikes several hours down the mountain to the town of Ti Guave where she purchases supplies for her business. With a 4,000 ft. elevation difference between her home and the town, carrying all these supplies back up the mountain is not for the faint of heart! Hermitha then travels farther back into the mountains by foot, to sell her products in markets several hours from her home. </p>\r\n<p>While this may seem like an extremely difficult way to make a living, Hermitha is thankful for this unique opportunity and has many dreams for the future. She dreams of buying a donkey to carry enough supplies so that she would only need to make one trip per week to Ti Guave. She also dreams of giving all her children an education. Hermitha is starting to see that dream fulfilled since two of her children are now able to attend school.</p>\r\n<p>For years these hopes seemed elusive, but now Hermitha and her children are watching them come true. The children are learning that hard work is worthwhile. Hermitha’s neighbors are also excited and ask how they can get involved in this program. One recently said, “This program has been a miracle for Hermitha.” </p>\r\n<p>And it truly has been. Thank you, supporters, for making it possible for Hermitha and others to experience the miracle of fulfilled dreams.</p>\r\n<p><a title=\"/programs/22\" href=\"/programs/22\">&lt;&lt; Back to SALT microfinance</a>\r\n</p>','2012-03-16 14:52:05','2012-03-16 14:52:05'),(69,69,'en','<p>{{ content_holder_109 }}</p>','2012-03-16 14:52:05','2012-04-18 14:39:17'),(70,70,'en','<br />\r\n<h3><strong>Thank you</strong> for your continued support!</h3>\r\n<p style=\"font-weight: bold;\">“Inasmuch as ye have done it unto one of the least of these my brethren, ye have done it unto me.” Matthew 25:40b</p>\r\n<p style=\"font-weight: bold;\"><img src=\"/system/images/BAhbBlsHOgZmSSI0MjAxMi8wNC8xMS8xOV8xOV8xNV81NjdfZG9uYXRpb25fYWRqdXN0bWVudC5wbmcGOgZFVA/donation_adjustment.png\" height=\"370\" width=\"613\" /></p>\r\n<p>May God richly bless you.</p>\r\n<p style=\"font-weight: bold;\">Sincerely,\r\n<br style=\"font-weight: normal;\" />Christian Aid Ministries | P.O. Box 360, Berlin, OH 44610 \r\n<br style=\"font-weight: normal;\" />T: 330.893.2428\r\n<br style=\"font-weight: normal;\" />F: 330.893.2305\r\n<br style=\"font-weight: normal;\" />E: <a title=\"camweb@camoh.org\" href=\"mailto:camweb@camoh.org\">camweb@camoh.org</a>\r\n</p>\r\n<p><a style=\"font-weight: bold;\" title=\"/home\" href=\"/home\">&lt; &lt; Go to home page</a>\r\n</p>','2012-04-05 20:32:47','2012-04-11 15:20:11'),(71,71,'en','','2012-04-05 20:32:47','2012-04-11 15:22:06'),(72,72,'en','<br />\r\n<h3><strong>Thank you</strong> for your continued support!</h3>\r\n<p>If at any time you wish to increase your sponsorship amounts, please call us 330-893-2428, email us at <a title=\"camweb@camoh.org\" href=\"mailto:camweb@camoh.org\">camweb@camoh.org</a>, <a title=\"/contacts/new\" href=\"/contacts/new\">send us a message through our website</a>, or write to us at <strong>Christian Aid Ministries, P.O. Box 360, Berlin, OH 44610. </strong>\r\n</p>\r\n<p style=\"font-weight: bold;\">“Inasmuch as ye have done it unto one of the least of these my brethren, ye have done it unto me.” Matthew 25:40b</p>\r\n<p style=\"font-weight: bold;\"><img src=\"/system/images/BAhbBlsHOgZmSSI0MjAxMi8wNC8xMS8xOV8xOV8xNV81NjdfZG9uYXRpb25fYWRqdXN0bWVudC5wbmcGOgZFVA/donation_adjustment.png\" height=\"370\" width=\"613\" /></p>\r\n<p>May God richly bless you.</p>\r\n<p style=\"font-weight: bold;\">Sincerely,\r\n<br style=\"font-weight: normal;\" />Christian Aid Ministries | P.O. Box 360, Berlin, OH 44610 \r\n<br style=\"font-weight: normal;\" />T: 330.893.2428\r\n<br style=\"font-weight: normal;\" />F: 330.893.2305\r\n<br style=\"font-weight: normal;\" />E: <a title=\"camweb@camoh.org\" href=\"mailto:camweb@camoh.org\">camweb@camoh.org</a>\r\n</p>\r\n<p><a style=\"font-weight: bold;\" title=\"/home\" href=\"/home\">&lt; &lt; Go to home page</a>\r\n</p>','2012-04-05 20:33:07','2012-04-11 15:25:21'),(73,73,'en','','2012-04-05 20:33:07','2012-04-05 20:33:07'),(74,74,'en','<p><img class=\"add-caption\" rel=\"450x450\" alt=\"Gosiane\" title=\"Gosiane\" src=\"/system/images/BAhbB1sHOgZmSSIqMjAxMi8wNC8xOC8wMF8yMl8xOF8xODNfZ29zaWFuZV8xLmpwZwY6BkVUWwg6BnA6CnRodW1iSSINNDUweDQ1MD4GOwZU/gosiane_1.jpg\" height=\"332\" width=\"450\" /></p>\r\n<p>Gosiane sits on a small wooden chair in her little boutique on the outskirts of her village.  Neat displays line the walls. Traffic roars and honks just feet from the open doorway, blowing dust and diesel fumes over her little store.  Gosiane’s 13-year-old daughter, her only child, helps attend customers. Two years ago, Gosiane’s husband was in a car accident, leaving him hospitalized for eleven days and unable to work for eighteen months due to head injuries. Gosiane and her husband had just started in the <strong><a title=\"/programs/22\" href=\"/programs/22\">SALT microfinance</a>\r\n</strong> program when the accident occurred. After the accident Gosiane became fearful. She was afraid that she would be unable to pay all the hospital bills. Her business declined during this time and she withdrew from the <a title=\"/programs/22\" href=\"/programs/22\">microfinance</a> program. But today she testifies with a smile that “God just took care of meeting our needs!”</p>\r\n<p>Once her husband was healed, they started again with the <a title=\"/programs/22\" href=\"/programs/22\">microfinance</a> program, and are now on their second loan.  Her husband has a part time job and Gosiane and her daughter spend most of their time running the store. She enjoys the lessons and feels they are a great blessing. She especially likes the spiritual teaching, and uses what she learns to encourage others in her village.</p>\r\n<p> Today, Gosiane has hope for the future. She has a vision of their little family store someday growing to where she can offer larger quantities to her customers. She would even like to expand into a larger wholesale store where other small stores could buy from her.</p>\r\n<p>Gosiane is very thankful, and her little business is growing. She now has a new little building that’s built with concrete blocks, and a concrete roof with a steel door and window. She no longer has to worry about the thieves who used to get in her tin shack and steal her merchandise. These are perhaps just little steps, but her family is thankful for each opportunity that the <strong><a title=\"/programs/22\" href=\"/programs/22\">SALT Microfinance</a>\r\n</strong> program has provided!</p>\r\n<p><a title=\"/programs/22\" href=\"/programs/22\">&lt;&lt; Back to SALT Microfinance</a>\r\n</p>','2012-04-17 20:22:56','2012-04-17 20:22:56'),(75,75,'en','<p>{{ content_holder_109 }}</p>','2012-04-17 20:22:56','2012-04-18 14:44:31'),(76,76,'en','<p><img class=\"add-caption\" rel=\"450x450\" alt=\"Viergelene with a bowl of cornmeal soup.\" title=\"Viergelene with a bowl of cornmeal soup.\" src=\"/system/images/BAhbB1sHOgZmSSIpMjAxMi8wNC8xOC8xN18yMV8wOF8zNDFfUDkwMTAwMTcuanBnBjoGRVRbCDoGcDoKdGh1bWJJIg00NTB4NDUwPgY7BlQ/P9010017.jpg\" height=\"338\" width=\"450\" /></p>\r\n<p>The sun is just peeping over the horizon as Viergelene’s young daughter clucks to the small donkey loaded with woven baskets overflowing with supplies for Viergelene’s business. Viergelene’s business is making breakfast in the market place.The donkey knows exactly where to go, but first needs to grab a mouthful of weeds growing out of the rocky market-place; the stick in the girl’s hand provides incentive to get moving. When they arrive at the market, the small girl unloads jugs of water, a small basin to wash up dirty dishes, and bowls and spoons to serve the food in. Before long, Viergelene arrives, carrying a bundle of sticks and a large cooking pot on her head. The booth is covered in cloth on two sides to provide protection from the wind, dirt, and the sun. A bench is set on one end where about four customers can sit and eat.</p>\r\n<p>Rocks are arranged in stacks to make three legs, the fire is started, and surprisingly soon, Viergelene is serving up bowls of “labouyi,” a thin soup made with cornmeal. For approx. $0.12 USD, customers can buy a good portion of labouyi.  Customers buy bread from her, tear it into hunks and eat it with their soup.</p>\r\n<p>Viergelene used to sell only bread, like so many other merchants in the local market. But since she joined the <a style=\"font-weight: bold;\" title=\"/programs/22\" href=\"/programs/22\">Shared Accountability Lending &amp; Teaching</a>\r\n<strong>(SALT)</strong> program in the summer of 2011, she no longer makes bread, but has found it is more profitable to buy it in quantity from a bread merchant and resell it. This enables her to focus on the parts of her business that are more profitable. Viergelene and her husband have no other source of cash income for their family of nine children. However, they do have a garden where the whole family works to help survive.<br />Veirgelene testifies, “Our lives are so much better,” she said with gratitude, “since we are in the <strong><a title=\"/programs/22\" href=\"/programs/22\">SALT</a>\r\n</strong> program!”</p>\r\n<p>Their family has to get up early and work hard to make this little business work, but she is very thankful for the opportunity. She would like to thank all who are helping her and her family reach their goals.</p>\r\n<p><a title=\"/programs/22\" href=\"/programs/22\">&lt;&lt; Back to SALT Microfinance\r\n</a>\r\n</p>','2012-04-18 13:19:03','2012-04-18 13:23:07'),(77,77,'en','<p>{{ content_holder_109 }}</p>','2012-04-18 13:19:03','2012-04-18 14:44:48'),(78,78,'en','<h2>Menius</h2>\r\n<p><img class=\"add-caption\" title=\"Menius (Min-eez) is a small-businessman who is not afraid of work.\" alt=\"Menius (Min-eez) is a small-businessman who is not afraid of work.\" src=\"/system/images/BAhbB1sHOgZmSSIpMjAxMi8wNC8xOC8xN18yOF8yM185NTlfTWVuaXVzXzEuanBnBjoGRVRbCDoGcDoKdGh1bWJJIg00NTB4NDUwPgY7BlQ/Menius_1.jpg\" width=\"450\" height=\"338\" rel=\"450x450\" /></p>\r\n\r\n<p><img class=\"add-caption\" title=\"Using money from a small loan from Shared Accountability Lending &amp; Teaching (SALT), Menius buys standing timber in the mountains of southern Haiti.\" alt=\"Using money from a small loan from Shared Accountability Lending &amp; Teaching (SALT), Menius buys standing timber in the mountains of southern Haiti.\" src=\"/system/images/BAhbB1sHOgZmSSIpMjAxMi8wNC8xOC8xN18yOF8yM185OTZfTWVuaXVzXzIuanBnBjoGRVRbCDoGcDoKdGh1bWJJIg00NTB4NDUwPgY7BlQ/Menius_2.jpg\" width=\"450\" height=\"338\" rel=\"450x450\" /></p>\r\n\r\n\r\n<p><img class=\"add-caption\" title=\"With his helper, he saws the usable lumber at his homemade sawmill.\" alt=\"With his helper, he saws the usable lumber at his homemade sawmill.\" src=\"/system/images/BAhbB1sHOgZmSSIpMjAxMi8wNC8xOC8xN18yOF8yNF8xMjJfTWVuaXVzXzMuanBnBjoGRVRbCDoGcDoKdGh1bWJJIg00NTB4NDUwPgY7BlQ/Menius_3.jpg\" width=\"450\" height=\"338\" rel=\"450x450\" /></p>\r\n\r\n<p><img class=\"add-caption\" title=\"Menius and his helper secure the logs with ropes and rip the logs into planks. It takes about one day to rip each log into boards that are ready to sell.\" alt=\"Menius and his helper secure the logs with ropes and rip the logs into planks. It takes about one day to rip each log into boards that are ready to sell.\" src=\"/system/images/BAhbB1sHOgZmSSIpMjAxMi8wNC8xOC8xN18yOF8yNF8xNjdfTWVuaXVzXzQuanBnBjoGRVRbCDoGcDoKdGh1bWJJIg00NTB4NDUwPgY7BlQ/Menius_4.jpg\" width=\"450\" height=\"338\" rel=\"450x450\" /></p>\r\n\r\n<p><img class=\"add-caption\" title=\"The work can be difficult, yet this opportunity has provided Menius with a reliable source of income to provide for his family of six children.\" alt=\"The work can be difficult, yet this opportunity has provided Menius with a reliable source of income to provide for his family of six children.\" src=\"/system/images/BAhbB1sHOgZmSSIpMjAxMi8wNC8xOC8xN18yOF8yNF8yMDFfTWVuaXVzXzUuanBnBjoGRVRbCDoGcDoKdGh1bWJJIg00NTB4NDUwPgY7BlQ/Menius_5.jpg\" width=\"450\" height=\"338\" rel=\"450x450\" /></p>\r\n\r\n\r\n<p><img class=\"add-caption\" title=\"The finished planks will be carried down to the local village and sold. Menius is able to earn about $13 USD per day from this small business, with part of these profits going to his helper.\" alt=\"The finished planks will be carried down to the local village and sold. Menius is able to earn about $13 USD per day from this small business, with part of these profits going to his helper.\" src=\"/system/images/BAhbB1sHOgZmSSIpMjAxMi8wNC8xOC8xN18yOF8yNF8yMzdfTWVuaXVzXzYuanBnBjoGRVRbCDoGcDoKdGh1bWJJIg00NTB4NDUwPgY7BlQ/Menius_6.jpg\" width=\"450\" height=\"338\" rel=\"450x450\" /></p>\r\n<p><a title=\"/programs/22\" href=\"/programs/22\">&lt;&lt; Back to SALT Microfinance</a>\r\n</p>\r\n\r\n','2012-04-18 13:36:45','2012-05-07 15:31:30'),(79,79,'en','<p>{{ content_holder_109 }}</p>','2012-04-18 13:36:45','2012-05-07 15:34:44'),(80,80,'en',NULL,'2012-07-30 15:36:18','2012-07-30 15:36:18'),(81,81,'en',NULL,'2012-07-30 15:36:19','2012-07-30 15:36:19');
